Snowflake follows a 3-layer architecture:

1. Storage Layer
Stores data in compressed columnar format
Automatically manages storage
2. Compute Layer (Virtual Warehouses)
Executes queries
Can scale independently
Multiple warehouses can run simultaneously
3. Cloud Services Layer
Manages authentication, metadata, optimization
